<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<TestCaseEntity>
   <description>As a CDAT user I want to change a forgotten password so I can access the system. 

Acceptance Criteria: 

RM-4327.1: CDAT provides a Forgot Password option on the login page. 

RM-4327.2: CDAT requires the user to enter their user name. 

RM-4327.3: CDAT sends a text message with a unique security code to the user 's registered phone number if the user selected SMS as an authentication method. 

RM-4327.4: CDAT generates a unique security code on the user 's registered Google Authenticator application if the user selected Google Authenticator as an authentication method. 

RM-4327.5: CDAT requires the user to enter the security code and answer the configured security question. The user is directed to the change password screen after answering the question and entering the pin code correctly. 

RM-4327.6: CDAT displays the following message if the user enters an incorrect pin code or incorrect security question answer: 

Please try again. Your account will be locked out after three unsuccessful attempts. The lockout will persist for one (1) hour. 

RM-4327.7: CDAT locks the user's account for a period of one hour after three failed attempts and displays the following message: 

Your account is locked. Please try again after one hour. If you cannot remember your log in credentials contact the support desk for reactivation.</description>
   <name>RM_4327_Reset Forgotten Password</name>
